doctype html
html(lang='en', xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1999/html', ng-app='peggerApp')
head
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge')
  meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
  meta(name='description', content='Pegger is a simple little two player peg jumping strategy game')
  meta(name='author', content='Erik Gillespie erik.gillespie@gmail.com')
  meta(name='favicon', content='/images/favicon.png')

  link(rel='shortcut icon', href='/images/favicon.png')

  title Pegger

  link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.2.0/css/bootstrap.min.css')
  link(rel='stylesheet', href='stylesheets/app.css')

  script(type='text/javascript', src='https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.3.0-rc.3/angular.min.js')
  script(type='text/javascript', src='https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.3.0-rc.3/angular-route.min.js')
  script(type='text/javascript', src='javascripts/app.js')
  script(type='text/javascript', src='javascripts/controllers.js')
  script(type='text/javascript', src='javascripts/services.js')
body(ng-controller='PeggerCtrl')
  .container
    .header
      ul.nav.nav-pills.pull-right
        li.active
          a(href='#/play') Play
        li
          a(href='https://github.com/egillespie/pegger-node-express', target='_blank') GitHub
      h2
        a.link(href='/')
          span.peg.r P
          span.peg.g E
          span.peg.y G
          span.peg.g G
          span.peg.r E
          span.peg.y R
    .jumbotron(ng-view='')
    .row.marketing
      .col-lg-6
        h4 Goal
        p
          | The game is won by successfully maneuvering a red 
          span.small-peg.r
          |  or green 
          span.small-peg.g
          |  peg next to the other peg of the same color.
        h4 Overview
        p
          | Pegger is a peg jumping strategy game for two players. On your turn, select a red 
          span.small-peg.r
          | , green 
          span.small-peg.g
          | , or yellow 
          span.small-peg.y
          |  peg and then select the hole 
          span.small-peg
          |  where you would like to move the peg.
        p
          | Players take turns moving pegs until either both red pegs or both green pegs are next to each other. Sorry, diagonals and yellow pegs don&apos;t count and you can&apos;t undo the previous turn!
      .col-lg-6
        h4 Rules
        ul
          li A peg must be moved into an adjacent hole or jump an adjacent peg into a hole.
          li Diagonal movement is not permitted.
          li
            | Only red 
            span.small-peg.r
            |  and green 
            span.small-peg.g
            |  pegs count toward victory.
          li
            | Yellow 
            span.small-peg.y
            |  pegs may be moved but are considered neutral and do not count toward victory.
          li A player may not undo the most recent completed turn.
        h4 Feedback
        | Have questions or feedback? 
        a(href='mailto:erik.gillespie@technicalrex.com') Email me
        | , I&apos;d love to hear from you!
    .footer
      p
        | &copy; 
        a(href='http://technicalrex.com') Erik Gillespie
        |  2016
